It has been revealed that Manchester United chiefs are not making any plan to sack manager Ole Gunnar Solskjaer. According to football expert, Julien Laurens, Solskjaer is safe and has been given the ultimate backing by Manchester United chief executive Ed Woodward. Solskjaer has been under intense pressure, especially since the 2-0 loss to Premier League basement side Watford on Sunday. Laurens told ESPN FC, “It is a question a lot of Manchester United fans are asking. “For now Ed Woodward and the Glazer family have some faith in Ole Gunnar Solskjaer and they are working together on the January transfer window. “It shows you that Solskjaer is going to be here in the turn of the New Year and I was told he will be there in the summer no matter what happens. “That doesn’t hide from the fact that he hasn’t been good enough. On Sunday was the one year anniversary and he just wasn’t good enough. “Yes there have been good results and performances against the top clubs and we have seen that this season especially. “They don’t know how to win games, they are not creative enough and they don’t have a plan B or plan C. “It shows you the limitations of Ole Gunnar Solskjaer in that job.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.